{
  "text": "306 cardiac cycles were acquired from 7 children or young adults aged from 2 to 20 (mean = 11+/-7y). This population was chosen because of the higher influence of vagal tonus at this age [CITATION_1] . Data were collected during conventional echocardiographies planned to monitor cardiac function. The examinations were scheduled more than one year after the chemotherapy treatment of a leukaemia or solid cancer. The patients' characteristics are summarized in Table 1 .",
